claim.claim-text:
1. A computer implemented method for high performance capability assessment of a pulp and paper industry, comprising:
defining, by a processor coupled to a machine-readable memory, a multidimensional pulp and paper industry performance reference set stored in the memory and comprising multiple key assessment performance reference tables, at least one key assessment performance reference table further defining a pulp fiber platform including:
a ‘Basic’ performance level specifying ‘Basic’ performance assessment criteria;
an ‘Intermediate’ performance level specifying ‘Intermediate’ performance assessment criteria;
an ‘Advanced’ performance level specifying ‘Advanced’ performance assessment criteria;

establishing wood and chip handling assessment criteria,
wherein the ‘Basic’ performance assessment criteria includes a first criteria where wood preparation for logs shorting, de-barking and logs chipping is done at mill site;
wherein the ‘Intermediate’ performance assessment criteria includes a first criteria where wood logs shorting and chipping is performed at mill site;
wherein the ‘Advanced’ performance assessment criteria includes a first criteria where wood preparation is performed at forest site and chips are transported to mill site directly;

receiving, through a communication interface coupled to the processor, an input specifying a pulp and paper industry area and a pulp and paper industry key assessment area with the pulp and paper industry area for analysis;
searching, by the processor, the multidimensional pulp and paper industry performance reference set for a matching key assessment performance reference table that matches the pulp and paper industry area and the pulp and paper industry key assessment area;
retrieving, by the processor, the matching key assessment performance reference table;
analyzing, by the processor, the matching key assessment performance reference table; and
obtaining, by the processor, a resultant performance level for the pulp and paper industry key assessment area.

4. A computer implemented method for high performance capability assessment of a pulp and paper industry, comprising:
defining, by a processor coupled to a machine-readable memory, a multidimensional pulp and paper industry performance reference set stored in the memory and comprising multiple key assessment performance reference tables, at least one key assessment performance reference table further defining a pulp fiber platform including:
a ‘Basic’ performance level specifying ‘Basic’ performance assessment criteria;
an ‘Intermediate’ performance level specifying ‘Intermediate’ performance assessment criteria;
an ‘Advanced’ performance level specifying ‘Advanced’ performance assessment criteria;

establishing secondary fiber handling and processing assessment criteria,
wherein the ‘Basic’ performance assessment criteria includes a first criteria where collection is randomly performed by dealers and brokers;
wherein the ‘Intermediate’ performance assessment criteria includes a first criteria where the collection process is partially structured, material is shorted by supplier based on it usage at mill;
wherein the ‘Advanced’ performance assessment criteria includes a first criteria where the collection process is structured and waste fiber is shorted at the point of sourced and then collected; and

receiving, through a communication interface coupled to the processor, an input specifying a pulp and paper industry area and a pulp and paper industry key assessment area with the pulp and paper industry area for analysis;
searching, by the processor, the multidimensional pulp and paper industry performance reference set for a matching key assessment performance reference table that matches the pulp and paper industry area and the pulp and paper industry key assessment area;
retrieving, by the processor, the matching key assessment performance reference table;
analyzing, by the processor, the matching key assessment performance reference table; and
obtaining, by the processor, a resultant performance level for the pulp and paper industry key assessment area.

5. A computer implemented method for high performance capability assessment of a pulp and paper industry, comprising:
defining, by a processor coupled to a machine-readable memory, a multidimensional pulp and paper industry performance reference set stored in the memory and comprising multiple key assessment performance reference tables, at least one key assessment performance reference table further defining a pulp fiber platform including:
a ‘Basic’ performance level specifying ‘Basic’ performance assessment criteria;
an ‘Intermediate’ performance level specifying ‘Intermediate’ performance assessment criteria;
an ‘Advanced’ performance level specifying ‘Advanced’ performance assessment criteria;

establishing pulping process assessment criteria,
wherein the ‘Basic’ performance assessment criteria includes a first criteria where sulfite process and Kraft pulping process in batch mode having total manual operation exists; and
wherein the ‘Intermediate’ performance assessment criteria includes a first criteria where Kraft pulping process having partially automated digester operation exists; and
wherein the ‘Advanced’ performance assessment criteria includes a first criteria where Kraft pulping process using RDH/super batch process with automated Digester operation control exists; and

receiving, through a communication interface coupled to the processor, an input specifying a pulp and paper industry area and a pulp and paper industry key assessment area with the pulp and paper industry area for analysis;
searching, by the processor, the multidimensional pulp and paper industry performance reference set for a matching key assessment performance reference table that matches the pulp and paper industry area and the pulp and paper industry key assessment area;
retrieving, by the processor, the matching key assessment performance reference table;
analyzing, by the processor, the matching key assessment performance reference table; and
obtaining, by the processor, a resultant performance level for the pulp and paper industry key assessment area.

